TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(1,8,1);
$b = random(1,8,1);
$c = random(1,8,1);
##P(x)=(x^2-$a x + $b)(x-1)
$b1=-1-$a;
$c1=$a+$b;
$d1=-$b;
$p = nicestring([1,$b1,$c1,$d1]);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Use the Factor Theorem to show that \(x-1\) is a factor of 
\[P(x)=$p.\]
$BR  
The function value \(P(1)=\) \{ ans_rule(10) \}.
$BR  
Thus, \(x-1\) is a \{ ans_rule(20) \} of \(P(x)\).
$BR  
EOT

$ans1 = 0;
$ans2 = "factor";
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(str_cmp($ans2));

